  "texts": [
    "For each context 𝑐 𝑡, the initial observation 𝑜 0 = (H, T, D) is composed of the user 𝑢's historical interactions H, tool description T, and demonstration D. The tools can be categorized into two types based on T 𝑡 𝑦𝑝𝑒, which can be either \"retrieve tools\" or \"rank tools.\"",
    "The description T elucidates the impact of using the tools, and D offers practical demonstrations of their application.",
    "Together, these components promote the effective utilization of external tools.",
    "Tool actions are formulated as T 𝑡 𝑦𝑝𝑒 [𝑎 𝑡, $𝐾], where T 𝑡 𝑦𝑝𝑒 ∈ {𝑅𝑒𝑡𝑟𝑖𝑒𝑣𝑎𝑙, 𝑅𝑎𝑛𝑘 }, 𝑎 𝑡 indicates the chosen attribute based on û's decision at time 𝑡, and $𝐾 specifies the number of items to be returned.",
    "For instance, as shown in Figure 1, at the first step, û opts to use the retrieval tools conditioned on the attribute \"genre\" and retrieves 5 items."
  ],
